==English==
===Etymology===
The word "Sunda" may originate from [[Sanskrit]], in which case it may mean either "[[light]]" or "[[water]]".
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Sundanese'''

# An [[ethnic]] group in the western part of the island of [[Java]] in [[Indonesia]], numbering approximately 31 million.  
# The [[language]] of the Sundanese people. The language is also known as [[Basa Sunda]].

===Adjective===
'''Sundanese'''

# Of or pertaining to the '''Sundanese''' people.

